setDesc.text: it that says "Out of order". The bell was like this last time you were here. Louis has probably left it like this on purpose - he likes his privacy.�Door:The door to this apartment is shut and no light shines from underneath it. It would appear that whoever lives here is out.�Door:This door is to Louis's apartment. It has his name written in a small panel on the front of it. Beside the door is a doorbell and a keypad.:Try using the keypad or ringing the bell.�Chair:Louis's overstuffed armchair:You can't, louis is in it.�Unit:These storage units are built into the floor. A microcooker sits on top.:If you open the units you will see what's inside.�Light:The hallway outside Louis's apartment is lit by this solitary green neon light. As a result the hallway is quite dark. The green light makes everything seem rather strange.:The light cannot be tampered with.�Doors:These doors lead out into the hallway. As you approach them they will open and then close behind you.�Vent:This vent must be part of the air conditioning system in this apartment block. Cool fresh air comes from it. It's a refreshing change from the air you have to breath outside:The vent is made of strong stuff and won't move.�Car:This car seems to be abandoned. Blue light from the pavement lighting allows you to see inside it where you can see that the stereo has been removed.:The doors are both locked, and I don't think it would go anyway.�Monitor:The familiar shape of a network monitor. Louis has almost the same model as you, although his is the worse for wear. Luois uses it all the time.�Toilet:The toilet occupies about half the space in Louis's tiny bathroom.:Do you really need to, right now?�Door:Another standard set of doors.�Bed:Louis's bed is in a mess. The covers are crumpled and the sheets have worn through to the mattress. The bed feels very lumpy and some of the springs are in danger of coming through.:You wouldn't want to.�Louis:Louis sits in his chair half asleep.�Drawers:This set of drawers is made of wood and it's probably the best piece of furiture in the room. Wood is expensive these days. You wonder where it came from.:To use the drawers you would have to open them.�Microcooker:A cooker the same as yours at home. Louis appears to be out of food. Everything he had he has eaten. Most of the empty packets are on the floor. Louis really is a pig.:You'll need to find a new packet of food.�Drinks machine:Louis's drinks machine will give you a drink, if you can find a cup to put in it.:You press a button on the machine and it bleeps at you. I think it needs a cup inside it to work.�Wash basin:A perfectly ordinary wash basin.:You turn the faucet and wash your hands. Looking around you cannot find a towel so you dry them on your shirt.�Faucet:The faucet is stainless steel and has hot and cold water coming out together. There is a temperature control on it that is set to the right temperature for washing.:You splash some cold water over your face.�Mirror:The mirror is fixed above the sink and reflects the rest of the small bathroom. A blob of shaving cream is stuck to the corner.:You admire yourself for a while and then realise you are in a hurry.�Toilet roll holder:It is fixed to the wall by two screws and is empty.�Pillow:This pillow was probably white once. It sits limply on Louis's bed.:Sleep is the last thing you have time for.�Guitar:Louis's famous acoustic guitar is on the bed. This is Louis's most treasured possesion.:You pick up the guitar and give it a strum. It is hopelessly out of tune, just the way Louis likes it. Carefully you put it back.�Interface:This Network interface is designed to take standard cartridges. They are placed in the slot at the front and then viewed using the monitor.:Place a cartridge inside.�Spill:Something has oozed out of one of Louis's food cartons and it sits on the floor looking horrible.:What on earth would you use this for?�Food:This food is cold and slightly mouldy. You wonder how Louis lives like this. His apartment is in such a mess:You really wouldn't want to eat that.�Garbage chute:This pull open garbage chute protrudes from the wall. To save Louis having to leave the house, he can throw trash away using this. It smells awful.:You don't need to throw anything away.�Comunit:You can use this to speak to someone who has just rung the doorbell, to see who it is. You have to be security concious.:There is nobody outside, and besides this isn't your apartment.�Shirt:One of Louis's bits of clothing lies in a crumpled heap. From the looks of it it needs a wash. Louis doesn't appear to have a washing machine.:I don't think you want to wear this. It doesn't smell too good.�Camera:This security camera records who comes in and out of the lobby.:The camera operates on it's own when someone enters or leaves the building.�Wiring:These two wires appear to be part of the network system. They disappear beneath the furniture to hidden connection points.:Louis would be devastated if you meddled with his Network, and disconnected it.�Keypad:The door entry pad to Louis's apartment is grimy and slightly sticky to the touch. It has the standard buttons for code entry.:You tap in the correct code.��Plaster:Gun damage is stewn around the floor.:Bish bosh, wallop.�Mugger:�Cd player:Louis has a CD player pretty similar to yours.:As you expected, it doesn't work.�������������������������������������������������������������������������������������

freeDesc.text: because it's been chewed.:You turn it over in your hands.�Plectrum:A red plectrum in the shape of a heart. It belongs to Louis. He buys plectrums all the time, but usually loses them straight away.:You are awful at the guitar.�Plectrum:Louis can never find a plectrum when he wants to play guitar. Now you know why, they are either scattered across the floor, or someone like you has wandered off with them.:You decide not to play the guitar.�Controller:This is the controller to one of Louis's appliances. You are not sure which one. It has many buttons on it.:You experimentally press a few buttons but as you look around the room nothing appears to have happened.�Food tray:This food tray has been used and contains a few remains of it's former contents.:There is no point using an old food tray, you can only heat up and eat from a new unopened one.�Food tray:A completely empty food oacket from Louis's flat. There really doesn't seem to be much point in taking this with you.:You can't, Louis got there first.�Cartridge:An unmarked blue Network cartridge.:You would need too place this in a Network interface first.�Cup:A cup that has "I love Illfracombe" written on it, only the "love" is replace by a big red heart shape. It belongs to Louis.:Place it in a drinks dispenser first. This one is empty.�Cup:This cup has a crack down one side, but that doesn't stop Louis using it. The handle looks as if it won't hang on much longer.:Take it to a drinks dispenser. At present it's empty.�Mug:A short wide mug. It has the word "Tea" written across it in large letters.:The cup is empty.�Bowl:A bowl that Louis is eating popcorn from. It's made of a heavy plastic and is designed to look as if it's made from wood.:There is no need to use the bowl.�Cigarette:A cigarette that is definately not synthetic. It belongs to Louis and smells quite strange.:I wouldn't if I were you. You need a clear head and smoking is bad for you.�Butt:A cigarette butt from one of Louis's cigarettes. He doesn't care where he throws them. One day his house will burn down.:It has already been used.�Butt:Another cigarette butt from Louis's apartment.:You can't, there is nothing left to smoke.�Butt:A small cigarette butt from real cigarette.:You don't smoke anything but synthetic cigarettes.�Toilet roll:A roll of toilet paper that is almost used:You don't need to, at least, not right now.�Cartridge:A green Network cartridge with a lebel on it that reads "This Is Araknafobe". This is Louis's favorite group and the cartidge belongs to him.:Place it in a Network interface.�Card:A membership card for a pool hall in the city.:The card can be used to gain entry to the pool hall.:The membership card is for a pool hall in the city.:Perhaps I should check this out.�Trainer:One of Louis's trainers which is thankfully almost new. The shoes fasten with a velcro strip. The the soles have a chunky rubber tread.:You are wearing the shoe already.:You slip the shoe over your left foot.�Trainer:One of Louis's white training shoes that has red stripes down each side. They are pretty similar to the ones you had before you got mugged for them.:You are wearing the shoe already.:You slip the shoe over your right foot.����������Shell:�Shell:�Gun:�������������������������������������
